 a huge plus.</p>\n<p>One of my favorite features is the easy-clean treat pocket. As someone who typically stores treats in a Ziplock bag, it’s been great having a pocket made specifically for treats. Cleaning the pocket is a breeze, and giving Micah a snack on the go has never been easier. I also love that every pocket is secured with a zipper. Nothing is worse than spilling your dog’s treats (or your own belongings) all over the ground, and that’s not even a possibility with this bag when it’s zippered shut.</p>\n<p>The built-in poop bag dispenser has been pretty great as well. Nothing beats the convenience of having a poop bag within reach the moment you need it and the fact that the dispenser is built-in means I’m less likely to forget them at home. It&#8217;s awesome that the treat pouch comes with color-matching poop bags, especially since the little dog faces on them are so cute.</p>\n<p>Along with being extremely practical for all things dog-related, it’s also stylish. It can be hard to find a dog-walking bag that doesn’t look tactical, so I was super impressed when I saw this one. It comes in 12 colors and looks like a traditional crossbody bag that you’d wear for everyday activities. I love how classy it looks, and I’m really happy with the blush pink color I got. It can also be styled in three different ways, which is super convenient for different outings. I typically wear it across my body, but the strap is easy to adjust if you prefer a different style.</p>\n<p>Thanks to the durable material, I was even able to use the bag in the rain. The outer lining is water-resistant, which is ideal for rainy days, and it’s easy to wipe down if it gets dirty. After getting dirt on the bag, I used water and a paper towel to clean it, and the spot that I thought would become a stain came right off.</p>\n<h2>Pros &amp; Cons</h2>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box