ooming" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">Dogster.com</a> for credit</figcaption></figure>\n<p>Similarly, claws should also be trimmed regularly, although they won’t need daily or even weekly trimming. You should regularly inspect your dog’s nails and cut them as needed. You may need to do this more or less often depending on whether your dog runs on abrasive surfaces often, and even just how quickly the claws grow.</p>\n<p>If your dog goes to a professional groomer, you can have them trim the claws, too, but it is a good idea to keep on top of this at home.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re uncertain about trimming your dog&#8217;s nails or are uncomfortable doing so, consult a veterinarian for guidance. You can also check out this <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-health-care/how-to-trim-dog-nails-at-home" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">step-by-step vet-approved guide</a>.</p>\n<p>Did you know you can talk to a vet online? Click on the image or button below to schedule a call:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://pangovet.com/talk-to-a-vet-online-dog-preventative-wellness/?utm_source=dogster&amp;utm_medium=article&amp;utm_campaign=dog_preventative_wellness/" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-763867" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/PangoVet_Mention-in-Content-for-PangoVet2-Preventative-Wellness-VMarch2025.png" alt="PangoVet_Mention-in-Content for PangoVet2 Preventative Wellness VMarch2025" width="2076" height="1076" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/PangoVet_Mention-in-Content-for-PangoVet2-Preventative-Wellness-VMarch2025.png.webp 2076w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/PangoVet_Mention-in-Content-for-PangoVet2-Preventative-Wellness-VMarch2025-600x311.png.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/PangoVet_Mention-in-Content-for-PangoVet2-Preventative-Wellness-VMarch2025-800x415.png.