5BB"></i> 3/4&#8243; Wide</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Satin Hybrid Buckle</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> The text beads say “Lorelei”</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p>The package arrived quickly, and the collar was neatly stowed in a ziploc-style bag. It was so compact that my mailman plopped it in my mailbox rather than by the front door!</p>\n<p>The first thing I wanted to do after taking the collar out of the bag was feel the silicone beads &#8211; I didn’t know what to expect from that and was so curious. The beads were so soft and comfortable, and had a slight squish to them in my fingers. I could tell they have just enough softness and flexibility to be comfortable for my dog, while remaining durable enough for any of her antics. I loved how vibrantly colored all of the beads are (very true to color from the website), and the “Lorelei” text was so easy to read from the text beads!</p>\n<p>The shape of the buckle also impressed me, as the buckle and biothane attachment both have a curve to them. I love how this collar sits on my dog, and the buckle shape plays a significant role in this. The steel D-ring is easy to clasp a leash to, similar to my dog’s other collars.</p>\n<p>Lorelei looks so adorable in this collar, and she didn’t mind it at all. After wearing it for a while, I think my pup forgot it was even on (she even took a nap with it, which isn’t something she does with her other collars), which is a big testament to how comfortable this collar is. My pup is a very polite leash walker, so it was easy to take her on a walk, and I could feel how sturdy the steel chain running inside is.</p>\n<p>Washing was a breeze, I didn’t even need to use soap! Just a quick little rinse.</p>\n<p>Although the website did mention that long-haired dogs may have their fur pinched and tugged in the collar, I haven’t had that experience with Lorelei (and she has quite the lion’s mane around her neck)! I think this is more a matter of making sure you don’t tug on your dog’s collar, especially if you have a longer furred pup. However, this is worth mentioning just in case.</p>\n<p>This addition to Lorelei’s collar closet is a welcome one. Being so unique, I don’t have anything quite like it, and I am helping her stay stylish wherever we go!</p>\n<h2>Pros &amp; Cons</h2>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Pros</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Cute designs</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Fully customizable</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Sturdy buckles</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Engraving options</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Easy to clean</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Handmade in the USA</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Open to custom requests</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#8c0000;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#bf000a;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Cons</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style