2319 47.8799 31.6582 46.7327 30.0109 47.0232Z" stroke="#639A9A" stroke-width="3"></path>\r\n            </svg>        </div>\n                    <div class="jump-links__items jump-links__items--custom">\n                <span class="jump-links__items--custom__hidden"></span>\n                \n<a href="#The_13_Home_Remedies_to_Help_Your_Dogs_Allergies">Home Remedies</a><br />\n<a href="#What_Causes_Allergies">Common Causes</a><br />\n<a href="#How_Do_You_Know_What_Your_Dog_Is_Allergic_To">How to Identify Allergies</a><br />\n<a href="#What_Is_the_Most_Common_Allergy_In_Dogs">The Most Common Allergy In Dogs</a><br />\n<a href="#Should_You_Take_Your_Dog_to_the_Vet_for_Allergies">When to See the Vet</a><br />\n            </div>\n            </div>\n</div>\n<p>Allergies can be a nightmare for dogs to live with. They can cause eyes to stream and noses to run. They also lead to itchy, flaky skin that manifests itself in scratching, nibbling, and biting. What’s worse, it can be very difficult to determine what’s causing these reactions.</p>\n<p>While there isn’t an easy cure, you can do something to help soothe and relieve your dog’s signs.</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-716645" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws oct 2024" width="1203" height="145" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-01-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 1203px) 100vw, 1203px" /></p>\n<h2>The 13 Home Remedies to Help Your Dog&#8217;s Allergies</h2>\n<h3>1. Daily Changes</h3>\n<p>Although a small minority of dogs are allergic to something in their food, most allergies are environmental.</p>\n<p>Determine where your dog walks and what they do before having allergic reactions and try to make changes to avoid the allergens that are causing problems. This might mean taking a different route while you’re out walking or preventing your dog from rolling in a certain part of the garden.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_622021" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-622021" style="width: 1000px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-622021" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Beagle-shaking-outdoors_Przemek-Iciak_Shutterstock.jpg" alt="Beagle shaking outdoors" width="1000" height="630" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Beagle-shaking-outdoors_Przemek-Iciak_Shutterstock.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Beagle-shaking-outdoors_Przemek-Iciak_Shutterstock-600x378.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Beagle-shaking-outdoors_Przemek-Iciak_Shutterstock-768x484.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Beagle-shaking-outdoors_Przemek-Iciak_Shutterstock-250x158.jpg.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-622021" class="wp-caption-text">Image Credit: Przemek Iciak, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<hr />\n<h3>2. Change Their Diet</h3>\n<p>If you’ve taken your dog to the vet and they have told you that your pup is allergic to a particular food ingredient, you should look for an alternative food that avoids those ingredients. There are many foods on the market, including those with unique protein sources that avoid some of the more common food allergens.</p>\n<p>Change their diet slowly to prevent diarrhea and gastrointestinal problems and make sure the food meets all of your dog’s nutritional requirements.</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>3. Install an Air Purifier</h3>\n<p>Some environmental allergens might be present in the air in your home. It might be dust mites or pollen that is triggering allergic reactions. An air purifier helps remove allergens from the air to provide fresh air that should prevent allergic reactions in your pup.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_607654" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-607654" style="width: 1000px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-607654" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/indoor-air-purifier-under-the-desk_Parinya-Smithijaroenpon_Shutterstock.jpeg" alt="indoor air purifier under the desk" width="1000" height="674" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/indoor-air-purifier-under-the-desk_Parinya-Smithijaroenpon_Shutterstock.jpeg.webp 1000w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/indoor-air-purifier-under-the-desk_Parinya-Smithijaroenpon_Shutterstock-600x404.jpeg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/indoor-air-purifier-under-the-desk_Parinya-Smithijaroenpon_Shutterstock-768x518.jpeg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/indoor-air-purifier-under-the-desk_Parinya-Smithijaroenpon_Shutterstock-250x169.jpeg.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-607654" class="wp-caption-text">Image Credit: Parinya Smithijaroenpon, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<hr />\n<h3>4. Oatmeal Bath</h3>\n<p>An oatmeal bath can be great for soothing itchy skin. It acts as an emollient, effectively holding moisture against the skin to reduce dryness and itching. You can create an oatmeal bath yourself for your dog by blending oatmeal into a fine powder and adding it to your dog’s bath water.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can use an oatmeal shampoo when bathing your dog. It will not only help to soothe sore skin, but it can also help to remove any environmental allergens that are lodged in the fur.</p>\n<div class="pnadl-cntn">\r\n<p>If you are looking for the perfect, pet-friendly shampoo and conditioner combo, we highly recommend the products by Hepper. With a soothing oatmeal shampoo, free of soaps and other harsh chemicals, and a cucumber and aloe scented conditioner, your pet's skin and coat will be smooth, hydrated, and irritation-free. </p>\r\n<p>            <div class="comparison-table">\n                                                                        <table id="wctable-764291" class="wctable">\n\n                        <tr class="table-head">\n                                                        <th class="wctable-head-col wctable-head-image">Image</th>\n                            <th class="wctable-head-col wctable-head-product-name">Product</th>\n                            <th class="wctable-head-col wctable-head-features">Details</th>\n                            <th class="wctable-head-col wctable-head-link"></th>\n\n                        </tr>\n                                                                            \n                            <tr class="wctable-row">\n                                                                <td class="wctable-col-image ">\n                                                                                                                                                                                                <a class="wctable-link" href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BSVRXJK3?tag=dogster-email-allergens-home-20&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" data-wpel-link="external">\n                                                                               