p-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-dog-wearing-harness-standing-up-outside-500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://joyrideharness.com/products/joyride-mesh-summer-harness?variant=43079446823108" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Latest Price</span></a></div>\n<p>I remember when I switched my dog, Micah, to a harness for walks, and it was seriously the best decision I made. It gave him more room to breathe, and I didn’t feel like I was constantly pulling on his neck. Over the years, I’ve tried different harnesses to see which ones work best for Micah, and I love finding new ones to use for the different adventures we take.</p>\n<p>When I learned about Joyride, I was excited to try them out. I love the look of their harnesses and there are so many fun colors, patterns, and designs to choose from.</p>\n<p>After browsing their selection, I decided on the Summer Mesh Harness. It’s not quite summer yet, but I like harnesses that allow airflow to keep Micah cool. This harness is perfect because it has a mesh design that is lightweight and breathable.</p>\n<p>When the harness arrived, it was packaged in a super cute bag with paw prints and pug faces on it. After opening the package, I put the<a href="https://joyrideharness.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external"> no-pull harness</a> on Micah to try it out. I had to loosen the straps quite a bit, but the large size fit Micah perfectly once the straps were adjusted (Micah is 54 lbs with a 28” chest). Next, I took Micah for a walk!</p>\n<p>My first impression is that this is a high-quality harness. It’s sturdy and stylish and has all the bells and whistles you need to make it extremely functional. It also does exactly what Joyride says–keeps your dog cool with the mesh material and helps you and your pup have an enjoyable walk with the no-pull technology.</p>\n<p>One thing I love is the EZ grip handle. This is amazing if you need to keep your pup close to you. There are several times on hikes when large groups of people (and dogs) come by, and I like having Micah as close to me as possible. I normally cinch up the leash so he’s by my side, but with the harness, I can grab the handle and have a solid hold on him.</p>\n<p>Joyride also includes 13 nametags, which are fun to play around with, especially if you like personalizing your dog’s walking accessories. It’s also great if your dog is a service animal or a puppy in training and you want to let people know right off the bat.</p>\n<p>Most importantly, I found the harness to be incredibly secure. I feel comfortable and confident taking Micah for a walk, and I have peace of mind knowing he’s safe. While it’s definitely thick compared to other harnesses, if you like having a firm hold on your dog, this is the one to get.</p>\n<p>If there’s one thing I struggled with, it was the Velcro strap. The strap is strong, which is great for keeping your pup secure, but it also means it’s hard to adjust. The good thing is once you adjust it for your dog the first time, you don’t need to mess with it again.</p>\n<h2>Pros &amp; Cons</h2>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Pros</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0p