ividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Key Features</h2>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-764045" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle.jpg" alt="Joyride Summer Mesh Harness Review - grip handle" width="1500" height="1125" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle.jpg.webp 1500w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle-600x450.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle-800x600.jpg.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle-768x576.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle-250x188.jpg.webp 250w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Joyride-Summer-Mesh-Harness-Review-grip-handle-500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="http://shrsl.com/4vfwu" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Latest Price</span></a></div>\n<h3>How it Works</h3>\n<p>The first thing you’ll do is pick out a harness style that you love and a size that fits your dog. Once the harness arrives, try it out on your pup! Unbuckle the clasp and slip the harness over your dog’s head so the Velcro strap is on your dog’s chest and the buckle is under their front legs. Adjust the straps until the harness fits snugly without being too tight.</p>\n<p>You can attach your leash to one of three rings on the back and there’s an EZ grip handle to give you better control over your dog and make taking it off a breeze. If you’re out at night, the stitching around your dog’s head and chest is reflective to help them stay visible, and the <a href="https://joyrideharness.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">dog harness</a> comes with 13 nametags that you can customize specifically for your furry friend.</p>\n<h3>Breathable and Lightweight</h3>\n<p>The claim to fame for this harness is the dual mesh (2.0) material. This breathable fabric keeps your dog cool on hot days so they can stay comfortable even in the most intense heat. It has three layers–a high-density inner lining that acts as a base, a stretchy interlayer that connects the base and the shell, and a breathable outer layer that maximizes airflow.</p>\n<p>The outer layer is a shell fabric designed with mesh holes to allow air to flow through, and all three layers work together to keep your pup comfortable.</p>\n<h3>No-Pull Technology</h3>\n<p>Joyride designs their harnesses to help you and your dog have an enjoyable and relaxing wal, no matter how strong your dog is. To make this happen, they included three rings for you to attach a leash to–one in the middle and two on each side. This way, if your dog pulls, they’ll end up facing you instead of pulling you.</p>\n<p>The harness is also designed to stop pulling without applying pressure to your dog’s throat like a collar would. This helps keep your four-legged friend safe while giving you greater control of your pup.</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster