Instapainting</span></a></div>\n<p>I have always been a big admirer of traditional art, and as mentioned in the intro, art of my dog is absolutely what I’d like hanging in my home! I wouldn’t even know where to begin with that for myself, so Instapainting was something I was eager to try.</p>\n<p>I started by selecting the kind of painting I wanted, and although all mediums produce great work, oil painting is something I wanted to use to capture my pup’s personality. I also really like how smooth and vibrant that medium is, as I planned to provide a very colorful reference image that matches with the decor of my home. Instapainting made the ordering process very simple, providing a few options to choose from.</p>\n<p>The options I selected were:</p>\n<div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Size &#8211; 16&#8243; x 20&#8243;</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Number of subjects &#8211; 1 Subject</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Artist Location &#8211; Global Artists &amp; Studios</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Finishing Option &#8211; Rolled</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Methodology &#8211; Enhanced Accuracy</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Can we use this as a portfolio piece? &#8211; Yes</em></li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> <em>Delivery Deadline &#8211; Standard Delivery (approx 3 weeks)</em></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p>Once the order was placed, I received an email from Instapainting stating that several artists would offer their painting styles up for me to choose from. Once the artists had populated the Artist and Studio Responses page, I was able to scroll through them all, view their portfolios, and see if they would charge an additional fee to use or not.</p>\n<p>Instapainting automatically highlighted the artist that they felt fit my criteria the best, and that was Peter Lin, whom I ended up selecting! After selecting Peter, the correspondence started. He asked me if I had any requests for him, if I wanted the painting adjusted in size to fit the composition, and more. I found Peter to be very communicative, and the platform was easy to use.</p>\n<p>Although I liked this hands-on approach, my only little critique would be that I had no idea that this would be the process. Based on the website, I didn’t catch the fact that you need to wait for artists to apply, and then you have to spend time selecting them. This did make the painting process longer because I had assumed that Instapainting would automatically match me with someone and the painting would have already been started. Had I missed their email, I would have been confused about why no progress was made!</p>\n<p>At a midpoint in the process, Peter sent me a photograph of the painting he had done. From here, Instapainting created a fantastic platform to better explain to an artist any changes you may want to be made. I was fortunate to like what Peter did and not request any changes. However, for those who want to make changes, Instapainting allows you to create annotations to make your adjustments very clear to the artist.</p>\n<p>When I considered the painting finished, I marked it on the website and told Peter I was ready for it! He responded that the painting would be shipped as soon as it was dry. This process took 7 days for him to ship it. I was definitely not in a rush, but be aware that this can add significant time to your order’s process.</p>\n<p>The painting arrived very carefully packaged, with a lot of attention to detail to ensure nothing was damaged in the process. I was beside myself with how much I loved the painting, it was absolutely beautiful! Even more detailed in person, with Peter masterfully capturing my dog’s expression and personality. I quickly framed the canvas and am thoroughly enjoying this gorgeous artwork! I think my pup might be too!</p>\n<h3>Pros &amp; Cons</h3>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Pros</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Easy process &amp; custom result</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Choice of different art mediums</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Many sizes available</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Lots of artists to choose from</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Payment plans available</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#8c0000;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#bf000a;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Cons</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Longer process to start</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Artist shipped painting later than expected</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-div