Oil-Review-product-with-dog-eating-in-the-background-768x576.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Brothers-Apothecary-Calming-K-9-CBD-Oil-Review-product-with-dog-eating-in-the-background-250x188.jpg.webp 250w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Brothers-Apothecary-Calming-K-9-CBD-Oil-Review-product-with-dog-eating-in-the-background-500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://www.thebrothersapothecary.com/product/calming-k9-cbd-oil-for-dogs/" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Price on The Brothers Apothecary</span></a></div>\n<p>I have been using CBD for my two senior dogs for the last few years. Ragz, my 14-year-old Dalmatian mix, struggles with sore joints in her old age. And my 16-year-old Chihuahua, Papyrus, has some arthritis in his back legs, anxiety, and trouble sleeping now that he’s older.</p>\n<p>I’ve found that quality CBD oil really has a profound effect on these issues, helping both my dogs find relief. Unfortunately, with both dogs requiring therapeutic doses of the stuff twice every day, the cost can quickly add up. Because of this, I’m always on the lookout for well-priced, quality pet CBD options.</p>\n<p>And that’s why I was so excited to try this tincture from The Brothers Apothecary.</p>\n<p>Not only is this CBD oil made from simple quality ingredients, but it’s also a high-concentration formula and very affordable. All in all, this product looks great on paper, but I still had to put it to the test to find out if it was as effective as advertised.</p>\n<h3>What I Liked</h3>\n<p>To start, I’m a big fan of the ingredients that make up this CBD oil tincture. I also LOVE the price.</p>\n<p>Calming K-9 CBD Oil contains only full spectrum hemp extract, MCT oil, and French-style peanut butter oil. There are zero filler ingredients, and the taste used is all-natural and potent.</p>\n<p>I’ve already mentioned how affordable this oil is, which is why I was so surprised to learn that each bottle has an impressive 500mg of CBD. For pet CBD oil, this is a fairly high concentration. And for a dog owner who goes through a lot of CBD, it’s exactly what I like to see.</p>\n<p>Not only do high-concentration formulas make for less added oil in your dog’s meals, but the bottles also last a lot longer, which means even more cost savings.</p>\n<p>I added this product to my dogs&#8217; meals twice a day at their typical therapeutic dose (15mg for Ragz, and 4mg for Papyrus). They had been off CBD for a few months due to some backorder issues with my usual brand, which provided the perfect environment to test this oil.</p>\n<p>I first noticed results after about two weeks of continual use. Both dogs appeared less stiff and sore in the morning. There was also a clear difference in their mobility on walks starting around this time.</p>\n<p>I have been using it for three weeks now and have just started to notice a difference in Papyrus’ anxiety. He seems calmer throughout the day and is sleeping much more soundly overnight. I’m hopeful that these effects will continue to build over the next couple of weeks.</p>\n<h3>Where I Saw Room for Improvement</h3>\n<p>Honestly, there isn’t much I don’t love about this CBD oil. And my dogs seem to agree.</p>\n<p>They happily eat it when I mix it in with their food. And will swallow it when I put it directly in their mouth, though this is not their favorite method of administration.</p>\n<p>I only ran into two issues with this product.</p>\n<p>First, I had a bit of trouble with the dropper. It has volume markers on the pipette, which makes measuring the correct amount super easy. However, for some reason, squeezing the rubber bulb doesn’t fully empty the pipette.</p>\n<p>This was problematic when trying to give Papyrus his small dose. I haven’t had this issue with other CBD oils, but it’s possible this is an uncommon defect that others won’t experience.</p>\n<p>The other issue I ran into was finding the third-party lab results for the batch I received on the company’s webpage. The QR code on the bottle only brings me to the lab results home page and there is no category listed for “pet oils” or “tinctures.” When I was not able to locate the batch number even after sifting through all the lab results on the page, I contacted The Brothers Apothecary through their Contact Me page and using the phone number on their website. It took about a week to hear back but I did receive the information I was looking for.</p>\n<p>Despite these minor issues, I have been really impressed with this company and this product and will continue to use it. At this price, how could I not?!</p>\n<h2>Pros &amp; Cons</h2>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Pros</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> High concentration</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Simple ingredients</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Full spectrum</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Natural peanut oil for flavor</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Easy to dose</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color