div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Isn’t made with any beef</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> The primary ingredient is chicken</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Made with meat by-products and carrageenan</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Contains added color and preservatives</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Buyer&#8217;s Guide: How to Pick the Best Canned &amp; Wet Dog Foods</h2>\n<p>Before you make any decisions, read through our buyer’s guide. We go over a few points that are worth considering before you make your purchase.</p>\n<h3>Flavor</h3>\n<p>If your dog enjoys certain flavors and not others, you should avoid variety packs. On the other hand, if you have a new dog and still haven’t figured out their likes and dislikes, a variety pack is a great way to experiment so you can figure out your dog’s favorites.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_45461" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-45461" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-45461" src="https://dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/labrador-retriever-eating-dog-food_Jaromir-Chalabala_Shutterstock.jpg" alt="labrador retriever eating dog food" width="810" height="540" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-45461" class="wp-caption-text">Image Credit: Jaromir Chalabala, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<p>Most pet owners <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/how-to-choose-dog-food/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">don’t bother reading the ingredient list</a>, but this is a great habit to get into. If you’re not too concerned about what is in your dog’s food and they don’t have any health issues, you can choose to read the ingredients or not. But many manufacturers include ingredients that you might want to avoid. The rule of thumb is that the first five ingredients should be whole ingredients and real meat.</p>\n<p>If you need veterinary advice over your dog&#8217;s nutrition, we recommend speaking with a vet.</p>\n<p><span data-sheets-root="1"><p><div class="su-box su-box-style-default pangovet-mention-box" id="" style="border-color:#003e92;border-radius:3px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#0971c5;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:1px;border-top-right-radius:1px">💛 🐶 Speak To a Vet Online From the Comfort of Your Couch!</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:1px;border-bottom-right-radius:1px"> <img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-3542157 chewy-in-content-image" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/PangoVet_Mention-in-Content_v10_Oct-18-2024-copy.png" alt="PangoVet" width="375" /></p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: 500; text-align: center; line-height: 1.5; font-size: medium !important; margin-bottom: 20px;">If you need to speak with a vet but can&#8217;t get to one, head over to <a href="https://pangovet.com?utm_source=dogster&amp;utm_medium=article&amp;utm_campaign=dog-nutrition/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external"><b>PangoVet</b></a>. It&#8217;s an online service where you can <b>talk to a vet online</b> and get the personalized advice you need for your pet — all at an affordable price!</p>\r\n<p><div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://pangovet.com?utm_source=dogster&#038;utm_medium=article&#038;utm_campaign=dog-nutrition/" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:9px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 24px;font-size:18px;line-height:36px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:9px;text-shadow:none"> Click to Speak With a Vet</span></a></div></div></div></p></span></p>\n<h3>Are There Some Ingredients to Avoid Altogether?</h3>\n<p>Yes. As with human foods, some ingredients are best to be avoided completely.</p>\n<p><strong>Butylated Hydroxyanisole</strong> (BHA) is a chemical preservative that gets added to fats and oils. Even small amounts of BHA can be harmful to your dog’s health. The Centers for Disease Control even say that BHA is carcinogenic for humans and <a href="https://ntp.niehs.nih.gov/ntp/roc/content/profiles/butylatedhydroxyanisole.pdf" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank">studies show</a> that it can act the same in animals.</p>\n<p><strong>White flour</strong> is highly treated and stripped of most of its nutrients during processing. Its main function in dog food is to act as a binder and to add texture.</p>\n<p><strong>Meat meal</strong> is any unlabeled meat ingredient in your dog’s food. Companies tend to be very vague about what this ingredient is, which should raise red flags right from the get-go. These meats are usually made with low-quality, expired, or even infected meat. Meat meal can also contain fatty tissues, and dead animal remains. The purpose of this ingredient in dog food is to act as a filler. It has almost no protein and quality control is difficult to, well, control.</p>\n<p><strong>Artificial colors</strong> are used a lot in human food to make food look more appealing. The presence of fake coloring in animal food is completely unnecessary. We don’t need to find the appearance of our dog’s food to be appealing. All that matters is that your dog finds it appealing, and chances are he will put a lot more stock into the scent and texture of the food than its color.</p>\n<p><strong>Farmed salmon</strong> might sound like a healthy ingredient to have in your pup’s food, but it’s not. Many dogs are interested in eating fish, salmon included. Farmed salmon, though, can include harmful toxins that can be dangerous for your pup. Farmed salmon, including salmon meal and oil, can add high levels of mercury and other fat-soluble toxins into their diet. This type of salmon can contain <a href="https://www.onemedical.com/blog/eat-well/farmed-salmon/#:~:text=The%20majority%20of,develop%20it%20naturally)." target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">toxic chemicals</a> and cancer-causing PCBs.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_169452" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-169452" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-169452" src="https://dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/close-up-of-a-dog-eating-from-the-bowl_Dmytro-Zinkevych_Shutterstock.jpg" alt="close up of a dog eating from the bowl" width="810" height="540" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-169452" class="wp-caption-text">Image By: Dmytro Zinkevych, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<h3>Read Everything</h3>\n<p>Always double-check every aspect of the food before you buy it. Is it pâté or shredded? Does it contain real, whole meat, or just flavors? If your <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-canned-wet-dog-food-for-sensitive-stomachs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">dog is sensitive to specific ingredients</a>, like chicken, make sure it doesn’t include any.</p>\n<h3>Size</h3>\n<p>The larger your dog, the more you have to buy. Aim for large cans because they won’t sit in the fridge for long, and you’ll get one or two servings from each can. You should aim for small containers for your small dogs. If you purchase 13-ounce cans for your Chihuahua, they will end up sitting in the fridge for a long time. The size of the can/container should be relative to the size of your dog and how much they can eat in one meal.</p>\n<h3>Is Wet Food Better Than Dry Food?</h3>\n<p><a href="https://petkeen.com/how-much-wet-food-should-you-feed-dogs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Wet food</a> can sometimes provide more benefits for your dog than dry food.</p>\n<p>Wet foods have a higher moisture content, which is very beneficial for dogs who might not drink as much water as they should. It’s also great for dogs with certain medical conditions that necessitate a proper amount of hydration, like kidney disease.</p>\n<p>Canned food also tends to be more palatable to most dogs. It has aromas that dry food does not and may also be more flavorful. Offering wet foods is <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/how-much-canned-food-to-feed-a-dog" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">a great way to entice your dog to eat</a> if they’re sick or have a low appetite.</p>\n<p>Wet foods can help increase satiety. This is beneficial for dogs who need assistance with weight loss as it will help them feel fuller for longer after meals. Finally, wet foods are, by nature, simpler to chew. If your dog has dental disease or other oral concerns, he might be more apt to eat wet food because of how easy it is to eat.</p>\n<p>Now, that’s not to say that dry food doesn’t have its list of benefits. It can be more convenient as portioning it out is easier. Dry food is often more affordable and can work well as a food enrichment item in puzzle toys and automatic feeders.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_120246" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-120246" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-120246" src="https://dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/dog-automatic-feeder_muslody.com-Shutterstock.jpg" alt="dog automatic feeder" width="810" height="540" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-120246" class="wp-caption-text">Image By: muslody.com, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<h2>Our Selection Process For Canned &amp; Wet Dog Foods</h2>\n<p>To create this buyer&#8217;s guide, our writing team and editorial staff checked customer reviews, brand reputation, and veterinary approval ratings to present the dog foods we think should be highlighted for our readers. In some cases, we conducted hands-on testing along with seeing how much our dogs liked the dog foods. All these factors were considered when selecting these listed dog foods to help you make the best purchase for your furry friends.</p>\n<h2>Why Trust Dogster?</h2>\n<p>Since 2004, Dogster has been a trusted brand for dog owners online, which means we have a lot of experience with dog foods. We take pride in promoting the well-being of all dogs—from toy breeds to giant canines. Our in-house veterinarians, writers, and editors examine each product on our lists, ensuring its quality and reputation. As pet owners ourselves, we only want the best for our furry companions. At Dogster, we are transparent about the products we promote. The nutritional information, overall brand reputation, and customer reviews are all considered for these lists. We inform you how we want to be informed.</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Final Verdict</h2>\n<p>Our pick for the best wet dog food is <a href="https://olliepets.sjv.io/Ygo7gP" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank">Ollie</a> because of its human-grade meat ingredients and quality service. Our pick for best canned dog food for the money is <a href="https://www.dogster.com/redirects/?url=https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l8LeP/pubref:dogsteremailcannedwet/destination:https://www.chewy.com/natures-recipe-variety-pack-grain/dp/234457" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Nature’s Recipe Variety Pack Grain-Free Wet Dog Food</a> because it’s grain-free and an all-natural stew for your pup. Finally, <a href="https://www.dogster.com/recommendations/the-farmers-dog-food" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_blank">The Farmer’s Dog delivery service</a> is expensive, but it’s excellent food for dogs of all ages, sizes, and breeds.</p>\n<p>Hopefully, our reviews of the best canned and wet dog food have at least started you on the path to <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-canned-wet-dog-foods-for-small-dogs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">finding the right food for your pup</a>. Our dogs only deserve the best!</p>\n<p><strong>See Also:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-moist-dog-foods/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">11 Best Moist Dog Foods – Reviews &amp; Top Picks</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-wet-dog-foods-uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">8 Best Wet Dog Foods in the UK – Reviews &amp; Top Picks</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p>Featured Image Credit: chaoss, Shutterstock</p>\n<p>The post <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-canned-wet-dog-food-updated">11 Best Canned &#038; Wet Dog Foods in 2025 &#8211; Reviews &#038; Top Picks</a> by <a href="https://www.dogster.com/author/dogedit">Dogster Team</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.dogster.com">Dogster</a>. Copying over entire articles infringes on copyright laws. You may not be aware of it, but all of these articles were assigned, contracted and paid for, so they aren't considered public domain. However, we appreciate that you like the article and would love it if you continued sharing just the first paragraph of an article, then linking out to the rest of the piece on Dogster.com.</p>\n	The post 11 Best Canned &#038; Wet Dog Foods in 2025 &#8211; Reviews &#038; Top Picks by Dogster Team appeared first on Dogster. Copying over entire articles infringes on copyright laws.	dogexpress	https://www.dogster.com/dog-nutrition/best-canned-wet-dog-food-updated	https://dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/shih-tzu-dog-getting-wet-food-from-owner-at-kitchen_chaoss_Shutterstock.jpg	2025-03-26 00:26:34	2025-04-09 23:04:11.902439	["Dog Nutrition", "b