sync" class="size-full wp-image-698711" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock.jpg" alt="A nice German shepherd dog takes a bath with soap" width="1000" height="667" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock-600x400.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock-800x534.jpg.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock-768x512.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/A-nice-German-shepherd-dog-takes-a-bath-with-soap_Korneeva-Kristina_Shutterstock-250x167.jpg.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-698711" class="wp-caption-text">Image Credit: Korneeva Kristina, Shutterstock</figcaption></figure>\n<p>When purchasing dog shampoo, consider the ingredients and find something that works for your dog. There are a couple of do’s and don’ts.</p>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Do's</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Look for natural ingredients.</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Search for soap-free shampoos.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#8c0000;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#bf000a;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Don'ts</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Choose a shampoo that has dyes or paraben.</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Buy a shampoo without checking the ingredients.</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Use human shampoo for your pup.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p>If your dog is still young, choose a puppy-appropriate shampoo that is gentler and has a no-tear recipe. You can also make a <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-health-care/diy-dog-shampoos-with-coconut-oil" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">DIY homemade dog shampoo.</a></p>\n<div class="pnadl-cntn">\r\n<p><strong>Our Favorite Products</strong></p>\r\n<p>Selecting the right shampoo and conditioner makes the world of a difference when grooming your pup. Our favorite products are the duo by Hepper. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BSVRXJK3?tag=dogster-email-shampoo-expire-20&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Oatmeal Pet Shampoo</a> is formulated with aloe and oatmeal to soothe skin and hydrate the coat. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CPP5J8D8?tag=dogster-email-shampoo-expire-20&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Pet Conditioner</a> works at eliminating tangles and ta