trong></td>\n<td width="290">Dogs and cats that are up to 16&#8243; in length lying down and 15 lbs in weight</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Price Range:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">Mid-range</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Contents:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">Carrier, interior bedding, straps, collapsible bowl, gel potty pads</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Specs:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">17.5&#8243; Exterior Length x 10.5&#8243; Width x 11&#8243; Height at 3.4lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Color Options:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">Platinum gray, Deja blue, charcoal ash, rosa, and lavender</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Assembly:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">Easy and quick pop-up and zip-up assembly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Storage:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">A dust bag is provided for storage</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="90"><strong>Cleaning:</strong></td>\n<td width="290">Interior bedding is machine-washable, and the carrier itself is a wipe-down material</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Our Experience</h2>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-765128" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier.jpg" alt="Mr. Peanut's Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier Review - dog in the carrier" width="1500" height="1126" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier.jpg.webp 1500w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier-600x450.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier-800x601.jpg.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier-768x577.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier-250x188.jpg.webp 250w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-dog-in-the-carrier-500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://mrpeanutspetcarriers.com/products/expandable-airline-capable-tote?variant=29439029510167" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Price on Mr. Peanut&#8217;s</span></a></div>\n<p>Right off the bat I can tell you that this carrier has been used extensively, as I had a trip to Colorado right after getting the Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier in the mail. Before I even get into my experience, I want to express how incredibly thrilled I am with this bag &#8211; the features made flying so much easier (and less stressful) than any carrier I had used before.</p>\n<p>All of my carriers had originally come from Petco and were not collapsible. Color me surprised when this expandable carrier arrived at my doorstep fully folded with a dust bag! The carrier folds down quite flat and small, bedding included, which makes storage very easy. To build the bag back up, you just pull the center frame up and zip it into shape.</p>\n<p>Upon giving the carrier its shape, I could immediately feel how high-quality the construction is. The materials feel good in my hands and I kept discovering new features as I played with the bag. Even something as simple as the shoulder pad on the strap was well designed. My dog is 10 lbs, which isn’t particularly heavy by most dog owner standards, but definitely wears on your shoulder when carried for long periods of time. The shoulder strap is so well designed that the discomfort was well alleviated.</p>\n<p>Putting the carrier on the ground, my dog Lorelei climbed in without prompting or hesitation! My dog does fancy crates, kennels, and bags &#8211; but this was the first time that she had jumped in so fast. The faux fleece bedding gave her a cozy spot to rest, and she curled right up in comfort.</p>\n<p>As I mentioned before, we had a flight to Denver to catch. On our travel day, it was so easy to get this carrier from the car, to the terminal, through security, and onto the plane. I flew Southwest Airlines, which requires you to check in with an agent who weighs the bag, checks your pet, and gives you a luggage tag for in-cabin travel. This is the most stressful part of the experience, as they can deny your pet boarding for a number of reasons. As I am typing this from Colorado, I can attest that this bag fits all of the airline’s requirements in size, weight, and pet comfort. The bag breezed through TSA security with ease as well.</p>\n<p>While waiting at the gate, I used the expandable side to give Lorelei some more room to sprawl out. She loved it, and we got many compliments from strangers walking past. They were very enthused about the expandable side and how comfortable my dog was, as well as the aesthetic of the bag. I fly a lot, and this is the first time that a passerby actually stopped to talk about how nice the carrier looks.</p>\n<p>Another big stressor is making sure the bag fits comfortably under the seat in front once inside the plane. Passing the size inspection at check-in doesn’t necessarily mean your bag will be comfortable. On Southwest, it is an open seating policy, and I tend to opt for the middle seat because it actually has more room underneath than the window and the aisle &#8211; and as a rule, carriers do not fit in the aisle seat on most planes because there is an extra notch there. A kind gentleman invited Lorelei and I into the middle seat on the second row (we lucked out!), and the carrier fit underneath with ease. I didn’t even have to squish the top of it (which is why soft-sided carriers are recommended over the hard ones, you may need to squish a bit), it slid right in! The carrier even left room for my feet, which my previous one did not. Lorelei slept the entire 2.5-hour flight.</p>\n<p>Once we arrived, we grabbed a taxi to the hotel. Taxis can also deny you a ride if you have a dog, but the beauty of this bag is that it looks like a luggage duffel when all of the window shades are down (and you have a dog that doesn’t bark, like mine). I feel the leather handles and seams, along with the nice color, contribute to not looking like a “pet bag”. My driver had no idea I had a dog with me for the whole hour-long journey.</p>\n<p>Once in the hotel room, the carrier doubled as my dog’s kennel. I expanded the side so she had plenty of room. She slept in there comfortably at night, and I could zip her up without worry if I had to run down to the lobby to grab a plate of the complimentary breakfast or snag something from the shop. While at my work, the carrier continued to act as a kennel and Lorelei didn’t mind one bit.</p>\n<p>I see many, many years of adventures with this Gold Series bag, and wish I had it sooner.</p>\n<h2>Pros &amp; Cons</h2>\n<div class="su-row"><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#006600;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#009906;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Pros</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Clever features</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Compatible with most airlines</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Five colors to choose from</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Expandable for extra room</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Removable fleece bedding</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Easy to clean with waterproof lining</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Built-in luggage strap and car seat belt</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-check" style="color:#00bf08"></i> Self-locking zippers</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class="su-column su-column-size-1-2"><div class="su-column-inner su-u-clearfix su-u-trim"><div class="su-box su-box-style-default" id="" style="border-color:#8c0000;border-radius:0px"><div class="su-box-title" style="background-color:#bf000a;color:#FFFFFF;border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px">Cons</div><div class="su-box-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim" style="border-bottom-left-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px"><div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> The collar/harness clip is not removable</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-ban" style="color:#bf000a"></i> Only one small zippered pocket for items</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Key Features</h2>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-765132" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car.jpg" alt="Mr. Peanut's Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier Review - bag strapped in car" width="1500" height="1126" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car.jpg.webp 1500w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car-600x450.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car-800x601.jpg.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car-768x577.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car-250x188.jpg.webp 250w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-bag-strapped-in-car-500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://mrpeanutspetcarriers.com/products/expandable-airline-capable-tote?variant=29439029510167" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Price on Mr. Peanut&#8217;s</span></a></div>\n<h3>Specially Designed for Travel</h3>\n<p>To me, it feels like Mr. Peanut’s thought of <em>everything</em>. I never had a carrier so set up for travel like this one. The travel-specific features of the Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier include:</p>\n<div class="su-list" style="margin-left:0px">\n<ul>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Airline-compliant size and meeting FAA regulations</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Weighing only 3.4 lbs without your pet to not add more weight</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Luggage strap to attach to your suitcase</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Car seat belt strap to make vehicle transport easy</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Leash tether for harnesses inside the carrier</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Auto self-locking zippers all around</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Padded shoulder on the strap to make carrying for long hours less painful</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Name tag holder on the main strap</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Feet on the bottom of the bag</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Completely leak-proof</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Plenty of ventilation for your dog or cat</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Able to load pet from the top of the carrier or either side</li>\n<li><i class="sui sui-paw" style="color:#2575BB"></i> Zippered mesh pocket on the side for treats, supplies, or paperwork</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3>Many Windows With Expandable Side</h3>\n<p>I counted a total of 5 windows, all made of mesh with rollaway covers so you can customize where your dog’s windows are (or open them all for a nice breeze)! The windows being available on all sides (and on the top) is very convenient, I can have my dog enjoy a nice view on one side and block her view from distractions on the other side.</p>\n<p>The expandable side, of course, is a top-selling feature of the Mr. Peanut&#8217;s Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier &#8211; increasing the size of the carrier so your pup can sprawl out!</p>\n<h3>Bedding Included</h3>\n<p>Unlike other travel carriers, the Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier comes with bedding for both the direct inside of the carrier and the expandable section.</p>\n<p>The faux fleece padding with composite base insert goes into the primary compartment (and is easily removable). The bottom is velcro to keep it in place, and this padding can be unzipped and thrown in the washing machine.</p>\n<p>The faux fleece padding for the expandable section is zipped into the wall side, so when you expand, you just zip it down to line that section.</p>\n<h3>Easy To Keep Clean</h3>\n<p>Actual pet owners clearly thought out the design of this carrier, because the entire bag is simple to clean. For starters, the lining inside of the Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier is fully waterproof and leak-proof, making it easy to wipe up accidents. The outside of the carrier can be wiped down with water and soap in full, as the material is not bothered by moisture whatsoever. The faux fleece padding can be machine washed as well.</p>\n<h3>Packaged With Other Travel Necessities</h3>\n<p>Mr. Peanut’s Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier comes bundled with a free set of 4 premium gel pee pads and a collapsible water bowl! Both of these are <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-health-care/benefits-of-traveling-with-dogs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">must-haves for travel</a>, whether you travel by air or by vehicle. Take it from someone who commutes with their dog a lot!</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>About Mr. Peanut’s</h2>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-765129" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed-.jpg" alt="Mr. Peanut's Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier Review - collapsed" width="1500" height="1126" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed-.jpg.webp 1500w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed--600x450.jpg.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed--800x601.jpg.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed--768x577.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed--250x188.jpg.webp 250w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-collapsed--500x375.jpg.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p>\n<div class="su-button-center"><a href="https://mrpeanutspetcarriers.com/products/expandable-airline-capable-tote?variant=29439029510167" class="su-button su-button-style-default" style="color:#FFFFFF;background-color:#FF6600;border-color:#cc5200;border-radius:12px" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px 30px;font-size:22px;line-height:44px;border-color:#ff944d;border-radius:12px;text-shadow:none"> Check Price on Mr. Peanut&#8217;s</span></a></div>\n<div class="su-table breed-table su-table-alternate">\n<table width="623">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="130"><strong>Founding:</strong></td>\n<td width="250">Family-owned business based in Henderson, Nevada</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="130"><strong>Manufacturing:</strong></td>\n<td width="250">Most are handmade in Henderson, Nevada; others are sewn in facilities based in Vietnam, Cambodia, Spain, China, and zippers are primarily from Japan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="130"><strong>Shipping:</strong></td>\n<td width="250">Free shipping for the USA, country-dependent for International</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="130"><strong>Philanthropy:</strong></td>\n<td width="250">The company actively participates in the &#8220;Pay a Shelter Pet Forward&#8221; program by donating to and funding rescues, shelters, and animal welfare</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="130"><strong>Eco-friendliness:</strong></td>\n<td width="250">Certified cruelty-free, environmentally friendly, and ethically produced products</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-716648" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp" alt="divider dog paws 3 oct 2024" width="2560" height="308" srcset="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-scaled.webp 2560w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-600x72.webp 600w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-800x96.webp 800w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-768x92.webp 768w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-1536x185.webp 1536w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-2048x246.webp 2048w, https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Dogster_Website-dividers_v1_Oct-1-2024-04-250x30.webp 250w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h2>Is Mr. Peanut&#8217;s Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier a Good Value?</h2>\n<p>As someone who has used (and owns) quite a few travel carriers, I cannot begin to express my enthusiasm for just how worth every penny this particular carrier is. Although this bag appears similar to other types of expandable carriers, there are notable differences that make it top-notch against the rest (as detailed in the Key Features section).</p>\n<p>Priced at $109, the cost is actually quite a bit less than the “airline approved” carriers I frequently see at shops like Petco and Petsmart, and most definitely less than having to buy one at the airport itself! For a product that will last you trip after trip, it is well worth the cost.</p>\n<h3>How We Tested</h3>\n<p>The most straightforward test is to put the carrier on the ground and see if my dog gets inside of her own free will &#8211; much to my amusement, she hopped right in there the second I opened the door! I have always found this to be an excellent sign, as my dog can be rather picky.</p>\n<p>I proceeded to put all of the features themselves to good use, such as the expandable side, luggage slip, window folds, and more. The <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-health-care/dog-car-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">carrier traveled in the car</a>, on a flight, in a hotel room, at an outdoor park, and so much more. Cleaning was a breeze as I could easily wipe it down with a moist rag.</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-765130" src="https://www.dogster.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Mr.-Peanuts-Gold-Series-Expandable-Pet-Carrier-Review-owner-using-carrier.jpg" alt="Mr. Peanut's Gold Series Expandable Pet Carrier Review - owner using carrier" width="1500" height="1125" srcset="https://ww