ored shirt. Next, I uploaded a photo of Micah. Choosing a straightforward image is super important, so I looked for the most forward-facing, well-lit photo I could find. A few days after placing the order, Pupsentials emailed me a proof. I didn’t have any revision requests, so I gave them the green light to start working on the design.</p>\n<p>The sweatshirt took a while to arrive, but once it did, I was super impressed. The sweatshirt was packaged in a cute mailer and wrapped in Pupsentials-branded tissue, which was equally adorable. What really caught my eye though, was the sweatshirt itself. From Micah’s embroidered face to his name on the sleeve, this <a href="https://www.dogster.com/dog-breeds/cutest-dog-breeds" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">might be the cutest thing I’ve ever seen</a>! Not only that, but the fit is exactly how you’d want a feel-good sweatshirt to fit. It’s cozy and roomy without being too big, and the inside has a soft, fuzzy texture. It also has a classy look. It&#8217;s comfy enough to cozy up on the couch in and stylish enough to wear out of the house.</p>\n<p>Given the oversized fit and unisex sizing, I went with a size small (my usual size). I’m 5’1 and like having a relaxed fit, so this was perfect. Pupsentials doesn’t currently offer an extra small, but even if they did, I wouldn’t size down.</p>\n<p>Despite seeing a ton of amazing reviews (it has over 800 five-star reviews), I wasn’t sure how Micah’s face would turn out embroidered on a shirt. But after seeing the final product, I think it’s safe to say these guys nailed it. They captured Micah’s personality so perfectly, which I honestly didn’t expect with embroidery, and they created a perfect rendition of<a href="https://www.dogster.com/lifestyle/goldendoodle-coat-types" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"> Micah’s doodle fluff,</a> which I can imagine is not the easiest to replicate in a drawing, let alone stitching.</p>\n<p>While the